6?merchant=Home%20Depot" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Home Depot" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="9431" data-store="Home Depot" data-vars-store="Home Depot" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/9431/46402/4/167766?merchant=Home%20Depot" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$30</span> from <span>Home Depot</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>Heavy-duty garbage bags belong in your kit for several reasons: You can use them for <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/top-10-tools-to-help-you-ride-out-the-next-hurricane/#heavy-duty-garbage-bags">hurricane cleanup</a>, as a duffel for transporting stuff, as <a href="https://www.wikihow.com/Make-a-Trash-Bag-Poncho" rel="noopener" target="_blank">makeshift ponchos</a>, or as a small, basic tarp to keep supplies dry. A large-scale disaster could delay municipal garbage pickup for weeks. So you’ll want to stow trash in strong bags that can be kept outside without leaking or disintegrating. And you should have enough on hand so you don’t run out.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>After spending a decade in the building trades and shoving sharp objects into all kinds of trash bags, Wirecutter’s senior staff writer Doug Mahoney can personally attest to the durability of <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/9431/46402/4/167841/?merchant=Home%20Depot" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Home Depot" data-pick-type-id="1" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/9431/46402/4/167841/?merchant=Home%20Depot" data-vars-store="Home Depot" data-gtm-context="chapter_health-and-hygiene" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Home Depot" data-pid="9431" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/9431/46402/4/167841/?merchant=Home%20Depot">Husky 42-gallon bags</a>. The thick plastic even resists puncturing from broken glass and nail-embedded wood.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="light-and-heat" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="light-and-heat-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="Light and heat" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="5">Light and heat</h2></div></div><div id="light-and-heat-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="light-and-heat" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 bdfcf243"><figure id="attachment_333001" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image b71ff2c5"><img loading="lazy" alt="The UST 60 Day Duro Lantern, our pick for the best tabletop lantern." src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/08/emergencypreparedness-2048px-4731.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=320" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/08/emergencypreparedness-2048px-4731.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024" data-srcset="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/08/emergencypreparedness-2048px-4731.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024 1024w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/08/emergencypreparedness-2048px-4731.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024&amp;dpr=1.5 1536w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/08/emergencypreparedness-2048px-4731.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=75&amp;width=1024&amp;dpr=2 2048w,https://cdn.thewirecutt