e <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28205/146853/4/167855/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28205/146853/4/167855/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_communication-and-power" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="28205" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28205/146853/4/167855/?merchant=Amazon">BigBlue 28W USB Solar Charger</a> produced the most power of <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-portable-solar-battery-pack/">any portable solar charger we tested</a>. Yet it’s still small and light enough to fit into an emergency kit or go bag. Although other models nearly matched this pick for power and size, the BigBlue charger has unique features that make it more versatile and durable, including three output ports and weatherproof port protectors.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>It’s also a good idea to keep a <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-usb-battery-packs/">USB-A battery pack</a> or <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-usb-c-battery-packs-and-power-banks/">USB-C battery pack</a> on hand; we have recommendations to fit a variety of needs. Solar chargers produce power that you can pass to dying gadgets, but there’s no way to store that power for later use. Having a solar charger and a battery pack allows you to take advantage of the sun during the day and recharge smaller devices overnight.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><h3 id="disposable_batteries">Disposable batteries</h3></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><div class="ebb615ab global-cob eaaa9459 e1e566ad d097cc30" data-scp="callout"><h4 class="d02b79e1 e20b6350" data-scp="callout_label">Our pick</h4><div id="callout-chapter-1-20" class="fd1ac384" data-scp="callout_item" data-testid="callout" data-pid="10469"><span class="ddf294c5"><div class="fabe3ad3"><div class="e14704b2" role="button" tabindex="0" data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="10469"><span aria-label="Save Product" class="a478f5d2  " data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="10469"></span></div></div></span><div class="f1cabe17"><div class="f31f6df1"><div class="efc734d0 eae76d54"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" class="fa8c1483 product-merchant-link-button" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-store="Walmart" data-vars-store="Walmart" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="removed" tabindex="-1" data-pid="10469" data-gtm-context="inline"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/10469/fullsize.jpg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Duracell Quantum Alkaline AA Batteries" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Walmart" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="10469" data-store="Walmart" data-vars-store="Walmart" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">Duracell Quantum Alkaline AA Batteries</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" class="c44f6873" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="The best disposable batteries" data-store="Walmart" data-vars-store="Walmart" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_title" data-scp="callout_title" data-pid="10469" data-gtm-context="inline">The best disposable batteries</a></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">These batteries score highly in third-party tests for capacity and storage ability, and they claim to have a 10-year shelf life.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Walmart" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="10469" data-store="Walmart" data-vars-store="Walmart" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167795?merchant=Walmart" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$130</span> from <span>Walmart</span><br/><span>(pack of 24)</span></a><p class="ab4df9c8">May be out of stock</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>We <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/reviews/best-rechargeable-batteries/">usually recommend</a> cost-effective, environmentally friendly rechargeable batteries to power hardware that you can’t recharge or plug into a wall outlet. But during a power outage, rechargeable batteries aren’t very rechargeable. So we think it’s smart to keep a few disposable batteries on hand, particularly <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167861/?merchant=Walmart" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Walmart" data-pick-type-id="1" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167861/?merchant=Walmart" data-vars-store="Walmart" data-gtm-context="chapter_communication-and-power" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Walmart" data-pid="10469" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10469/193492/4/167861/?merchant=Walmart">Duracell’s Quantum Alkaline AA Batteries</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>Available from Amazon in boxes of varying quantities (and also available in <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/34102/155792/4/167873/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/34102/155792/4/167873/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_communication-and-power" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="34102" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/34102/155792/4/167873/?merchant=Amazon">AAA</a> and <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/57454/193529/4/167874/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/57454/193529/4/167874/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_communication-and-power" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="57454" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/57454/193529/4/167874/?merchant=Amazon">D</a> sizes), the Quantum batteries are crucial companions for flashlights, headlamps, and portable radios. They claim to have a 10-year shelf life. We haven’t tested them for a decade, but considering most alkaline batteries have a shelf life of <a href="http://www.batteryreview.org/disposable-batteries.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">around two years</a> before their stored power begins to degrade, these likely have a higher chance of being fully charged and ready to use when the time comes to pull them out of your kit.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="tools" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="tools-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="Tools" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="7">Tools</h2></div></div><div id="tools-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="tools" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>The key tools to have on hand for an emergency—everything from a road atlas to good duct tape—are also the key tools to have on hand for life in general. And here’s a common theme we noticed in this category: Although a great tool can be a genuine joy to use and will serve you well for years (if not decades), cheap imitators will waste your money and your time. Go for the good stuff.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><h3>Multi-tool</h3></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><div class="ebb615ab global-cob eaaa9459 e1e566ad d097cc30" data-scp="callout"><h4 class="d02b79e1 e20b6350" data-scp="callout_label">Our pick</h4><div id="callout-chapter-1-22" class="fd1ac384" data-scp="callout_item" data-testid="callout" data-pid="5860"><span class="ddf294c5"><div class="fabe3ad3"><div class="e14704b2" role="button" tabindex="0" data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="5860"><span aria-label="Save Product" class="a478f5d2  " data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="5860"></span></div></div></span><div class="f1cabe17"><div class="f31f6df1"><div class="efc734d0 eae76d54"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/5860/16784/4/167798?merchant=Amazon" class="fa8c1483 product-merchant-link-button" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/5860/16784/4/167798?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="removed" tabindex="-1" data-pid="5860" data-gtm-context="inline"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/5860/Leatherman-Skeletool-CX_20181211-180238_full.jpeg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/5860/16784/4/167798?merchant=Amazon" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Leatherman Skeletool CX" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="5860" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/5860/16784/4/167798?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">Leatherman Skeletool CX</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"><a href="https://www.n