?merchant=REI" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="REI" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="10199" data-store="REI" data-vars-store="REI" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10199/107690/4/167803?merchant=REI" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$24</span> from <span>REI</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>The <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10199/193515/4/167872/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10199/193515/4/167872/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_tools" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="10199" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/10199/193515/4/167872/?merchant=Amazon">Suunto A-10</a> is an inexpensive, high-quality baseplate compass that provides everything a novice orienteer needs to stay on course. The compass is made of scratch-resistant acrylic, with a fixed declination correction scale, a jewel bearing, and dual scales (centimeters or inches) so you can use it with maps that employ either unit of measurement. The A-10 even comes with a brief basic guide on how to use a compass and map—though you’re better off <a href="http://indefinitelywild.gizmodo.com/how-to-use-a-map-and-compass-1680534317" rel="noopener" target="_blank">learning as much about orienteering as possible</a> before you need to put the skill to use.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><h3>Fire extinguisher</h3></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><div class="ebb615ab global-cob eaaa9459 e1e566ad d097cc30" data-scp="callout"><h4 class="d02b79e1 e20b6350" data-scp="callout_label">Our pick</h4><div id="callout-chapter-1-28" class="fd1ac384" data-scp="callout_item" data-testid="callout" data-pid="16130"><span class="ddf294c5"><div class="fabe3ad3"><div class="e14704b2" role="button" tabindex="0" data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="16130"><span aria-label="Save Product" class="a478f5d2  " data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="16130"></span></div></div></span><div class="f1cabe17"><div class="f31f6df1"><div class="efc734d0 eae76d54"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/16130/48250/4/167804?merchant=Amazon" class="fa8c1483 product-merchant-link-button" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/16130/48250/4/167804?merchant=Amazon" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="removed" tabindex="-1" data-pid="16130" data-gtm-context="inline"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/16130/First-Alert-PRO5_20230316-192315_full.jpeg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/16130/48250/4/167804?merchant=Amazon" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="First Alert PRO5" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="1" data-pid="16130" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/16130/48250/4/167804?merchant=Amazon" data-g